items.name: RealCartoon-XL
items.description:
Want to buy me coffee? (Buy a cup)

Updates: 9/14/23: Uploaded Version 3! Hope you all enjoy. Been rather busy, so sorry for such a gap in the updates.

FYI VAE IS BAKED IN

Version 3 has https://huggingface.co/madebyollin/sdxl-vae-fp16-fix baked in.

RealCartoon-XL is an attempt to get some nice images from the newer SDXL. It still is a bit soft on some of the images, but I enjoy mixing and trying to get the checkpoint to do well on anything asked of it. This model level is definitely pushing my computer, so takes a bit longer to actually get it things tested and mixed :)

The mission is the same of the SD1.5 versions. Which is to get a checkpoint to pretty much do well on prompts while looking good with good variety

I hope you all enjoy it! Please review and share your images. I very much appreciate the support with the downloads and feedback (THANK YOU ALL). Never thought it would get this much attention.

The Process:


The starting checkpoints for merging were a couple of top ones of course (The checkpoints do/did not have restrictions on checkpoint mergers. Some of these are in my recommended resources as well). I also baked in the VAE (sdxl_vae.safetensors).

Currently this checkpoint is at its beginnings, so it may take a bit of time before it starts to really shine. I will continue to update it as time progresses...but I do hope you all enjoy it as it develops.

The Settings:

Still figuring out SDXL, but here is what I have been using:

  • Width: 1024 (normally would not adjust unless I flipped the height and width)

  • Height: 1344 (have not done too much higher at the moment)

  • Sampling Method: "Eular A" and "DPM++ 2M Karras" are favorites.

  • Sampling steps: 45 - 55 normally (45 being my starting point, but going up to 55 and even 60 a lot of the time)

  • Hires.fix settings: Upscaler (R-ESRGAN 4x+, 4k-UltraSharp most of the time), Hires Steps (10), Denoising Str (0.34 - 0.45 normally), Upscale (1.5 or 2 does well)

  • Clip Skip: 2

Some settings I run on the web-Ui to help get the images without crashing:

set COMMANDLINE_ARGS=--medvram --no-half-vae --opt-sdp-attention

items.name: Mint Candy Mix
items.description:
Mint Candy Mix is another open/free model with no license issues and it includes a cooking recipe.

This model aims to create a new, license-free merge model that mimics the output style of Aniverse V1.2.

Merged Models

  • candyMix by @mixboy : base model. Only output_blocks are modified

  • blessingMix by @mixboy : to add realistic output style.

Cooking recipe

Mint Candy Mix recipe

VAE

  • kl-f8-anime2.ckpt is baked in.

Recommends

  • version V1 has been baked with the kl-f8-anime2.ckpt. you don't have to load a VAE separately.

  • All posted images use "DDetailer script extension" or "After Detailer" for beautiful faces.

  • "EasyNegative" "negative_hand-neg", "ng_deepnegative_v1_75t" embeddings are recommended in the negative prompt.

  • Set Clip skip: 2, ENSD: 31337

Useful AUTOMATIC1111's webui extensions

  • SuperMerger extension

  • Lora Block Weight extension

  • webui model toolkit to examine LoRAs and models.

  • civitai extension to add several useful features for civitai.

ChangeLog

  • 2023/08/10 - first release out

License

All used models here have "Have different permissions when sharing merges" license permission, so I do not add additional restrictions on it.

CreativeML-Open Rail-M

This model permits users to:

✔Use the model without crediting the creator

✔Sell images they generate

✔Run on services that generate images for money

✔Share merges using this model

✔Sell this model or merges using this model

✔Have different permissions when sharing merges

Support me

items.name: Lucian Freud SDXL 1.0 art style lora
items.description:
If you like what I do please consider supporting me on Patreon and contributing your ideas to my future projects!

Lucian Freud art style lora for SDXL 1.0. Lucian Freud is a British figurative artist and now you can generate art similar to his style within your own Stable Diffusion workflow. This model was trained on 1024 x 1024 and is able to produce higher details and greater accuracy than if you were to simply type his name into your prompt.

I use this at a weight of around 1 but you may have to adjust the weight up or down to 0.8 incrementally depending on the complexity of your prompt. I used clip skip 1 for all of the images you see uploaded to this page. CFG 7 I think works good for this art style.

The main trigger is fr3u and there are no additional tags for this art style. Be creative with your txt2img or use img2img to guide the basic composition and colors.

Have fun playing around with this remarkable tech and if you like it be sure to review and upload all of your amazing works of art!

This LoRA improves yoga pants. It's quite simple but changes are noticable. It was created with 40 cropped images (768x768, without faces). If faces generates poorly use ADetailer.

Prompt: yoga pants

Other usefull prompts: from behind, back, standing, sitting

Be careful with "ass" and "bent over" prompts. Those may change pants into ultra skimpy shorts/thong or make your character bottomless. Fell free to try it yourself tho.😃

To change color You can use "[your color] yoga pants" or "[your color] pants, yoga pants". Both sometimes works and sometimes don't. You can also try adding weight - "([your color] pants:1.2)"

Recommended LoRA weight: 0.8-1.0

You can vote or give your idea for next trained model here! I'm gonna try to train most popular ones.

If you liked my lora consider buying me a Coffee or giving this model 5* and posting your creations😊

items.name: Mora Linda (Chalo | Las Lindas) | LoCon
items.description:
Mora Linda, Chalo's character, from the webcomic "Las Lindas". Works best on 1.0 weight. Training done on NAI.

This one is a LoCon which can be placed in LoRA folder on Automatic1111 1.5.1 so make sure to update otherwise place in Lycoris folder.

Trigger: "MoraLinda, furry, snout, colored skin, cow girl" always needed, for accuracy add "cow tail, horns, freckles, animal ears, toned, huge breasts".

Suggestions:

  • As this is a furry character not all models/checkpoints will be able to make her so test out several for best results.

  • Add "hooves" when prompting something with the feet visible.

  • "braided ponytail, long hair" for her classic hair style but you should be able to change it up a bit.

  • "animal ears" can be removed but may still appear sometimes.

  • "cow tail" can be used but she will try to gen tails naturally.

  • If you remove "furry" she will become more humanoid.

Fit cow girl big ol honkers this one was a request from comments and another good bit of with training monster girls to improve at training custom skin colors. I hope you all enjoy.

Feedback and reviews are always appreciated.
